<subSubSection lastPageId="8" pageId="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[160,1156,436,947]" box="[160,262,436,462]" pageId="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,436,462]" italics="true" pageId="7">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[160,1156,436,947]" lastBlockId="8.[160,1156,142,305]" lastPageId="8" pageId="7">
<bibRefCitation author="Lundbeck W" box="[160,353,473,497]" pageId="7" pagination="1 - 219" refId="ref13855" refString="Lundbeck W. 1905. Porifera (Part II.) Desmacidonidae (pars.). In: Hagerup H, editor. The Danish ingolf-expedition (Vol. 6 (2 )). Copenhagen: BiancoLuno; p. 1 - 219." type="book chapter" year="1905">Lundbeck (1905)</bibRefCitation>
in his monograph provided detailed descriptions of three representatives of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[401,479,507,531]" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="7" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[401,479,507,531]" italics="true" pageId="7">Iophon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that inhabit the Nordic seas and adjacent Arctic: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Vosmaer" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[1060,1150,507,531]" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="7" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="piceus">
<emphasis box="[1060,1150,507,531]" italics="true" pageId="7">I. piceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hansen" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[160,259,542,566]" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="7" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="dubius">
<emphasis box="[160,259,542,566]" italics="true" pageId="7">I. dubius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lundbeck" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[327,434,542,566]" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="7" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="frigidus">
<emphasis box="[327,434,542,566]" italics="true" pageId="7">I. frigidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Regarding the delimitation of these species, he suggested some differences mainly concerning style spination, the form of tylotes, and spicule dimensions in general, as well as the presence or absence of bipocilla. As Burton (1932) and later 
<bibRefCitation author="Koltun VM" box="[356,505,646,670]" pageId="7" pagination="1 - 263" refId="ref13426" refString="Koltun VM. 1959. Kрiмнiрogovыi gubki (iviрныk i daльнivo (tocныk мoрiй CCCР [Siliceous horny sponges of the northern and fareastern seas of the U. S. S. R.]. In: Pavlovsky EN, editor. Identifiers of the USSR fauna issued by the Zoological Institute of the Academy of Sciences of the USSR. Vol. 67 Russian. Moscow - Leningrad: Nauka, Academy of Sciences of the USSR; p. 1 - 263" type="book chapter" year="1959">Koltun (1959</bibRefCitation>
, p. 140 
<emphasis box="[593,606,646,670]" italics="true" pageId="7">–</emphasis>
150) noted, such minor differences may hardly be considered sufficient reason for species delimitation. Koltun examined 
<specimenCount pageId="7" type="generic">152 specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[269,347,715,739]" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="7" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[269,347,715,739]" italics="true" pageId="7">Iophon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and proposed two subspecies for the Arctic seas. The first, 
<taxonomicName authority="piceus" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="7" phylum="Porifera" rank="subSpecies" species="piceus" subSpecies="piceus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7">Iophon piceus piceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was identical to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Vosmaer 1882)" baseAuthorityName="Vosmaer" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[512,869,750,774]" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="7" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="piceum">
<emphasis box="[512,680,750,774]" italics="true" pageId="7">Iophon piceum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Vosmaer GCJ" box="[694,860,750,774]" pageId="7" pagination="1 - 58" refId="ref15169" refString="Vosmaer GCJ. 1882. Report on the sponges dredged up in the Arctic Sea by the ' Willem Barents ' in the years 1878 and 1879. Niederlandisches Archiv fur Zoologie Supplement. 1 (3): 1 - 58." type="journal article" year="1882">Vosmaer 1882</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hansen 1885)" baseAuthorityName="Hansen" baseAuthorityYear="1885" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="7" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="dubium">
<emphasis box="[882,1053,750,774]" italics="true" pageId="7">Iophon dubium</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hansen GA" pageId="7" pagination="1 - 26" refId="ref13160" refString="Hansen GA. 1885. Spongiadae. The Norwegian North-Atlantic Expedition 1876 - 1878. Zoology. 13: 1 - 26." type="journal article" year="1885">Hansen 1885</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lundbeck 1905)" baseAuthorityName="Lundbeck" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[294,613,785,809]" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="7" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="frigidus">
<emphasis box="[294,402,785,809]" italics="true" pageId="7">I. frigidus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lundbeck W" box="[422,605,785,809]" pageId="7" pagination="1 - 219" refId="ref13855" refString="Lundbeck W. 1905. Porifera (Part II.) Desmacidonidae (pars.). In: Hagerup H, editor. The Danish ingolf-expedition (Vol. 6 (2 )). Copenhagen: BiancoLuno; p. 1 - 219." type="book chapter" year="1905">Lundbeck 1905</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
were united under the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Koltun" authorityYear="1959" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="7" phylum="Porifera" rank="subSpecies" species="piceus" subSpecies="dubius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7">Iophon piceus dubius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the variety of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Koltun" authorityYear="1959" box="[551,799,819,843]" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="7" phylum="Porifera" rank="subSpecies" species="piceus" subSpecies="dubius">
<emphasis box="[551,799,819,843]" italics="true" pageId="7">Iophon piceus dubius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described by Koltun differed from both mentioned species. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lundbeck 1905)" baseAuthorityName="Lundbeck" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[541,862,854,878]" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="7" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="frigidus">
<emphasis box="[541,649,854,878]" italics="true" pageId="7">I. frigidus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lundbeck W" box="[670,854,854,878]" pageId="7" pagination="1 - 219" refId="ref13855" refString="Lundbeck W. 1905. Porifera (Part II.) Desmacidonidae (pars.). In: Hagerup H, editor. The Danish ingolf-expedition (Vol. 6 (2 )). Copenhagen: BiancoLuno; p. 1 - 219." type="book chapter" year="1905">Lundbeck 1905</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is characterised by the absence of bipocilla in its skeletal composition, while in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hansen 1885)" baseAuthorityName="Hansen" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[833,1107,889,913]" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="7" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="dubius">
<emphasis box="[833,930,889,913]" italics="true" pageId="7">I. dubius</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hansen GA" box="[946,1100,889,913]" pageId="7" pagination="1 - 26" refId="ref13160" refString="Hansen GA. 1885. Spongiadae. The Norwegian North-Atlantic Expedition 1876 - 1878. Zoology. 13: 1 - 26." type="journal article" year="1885">Hansen 1885</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
the bipocilla differed significantly in morphology (
<figureCitation box="[699,794,923,947]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1640,1663]" captionTargetBox="[164,1154,1006,1610]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[164,1154,1006,1610]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 4. Scanning electron microscope (SEM) images of bipocilla: (a) Iophon koltuni sp. nov.; (b) I. dubius (Hansen, 1885)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3654183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3654183/files/figure.png" pageId="7">Figure 4</figureCitation>
). In the case of 
<emphasis box="[985,1109,923,947]" italics="true" pageId="7">
I. p. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hansen" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[1035,1109,923,947]" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="7" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="dubius">dubius</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
the bipocilla have the identical, distinctly reduced alae, the length of which is half the size of the shaft of the spicule, and are provided with laterally arranged elongated teeth. The same distinctions from previously described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[838,916,212,236]" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="8" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[838,916,212,236]" italics="true" pageId="8">Iophon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species were mentioned for the specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Dinn and Leys" authorityYear="2018" box="[491,648,246,270]" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="8" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="nigricans">
<emphasis box="[491,497,246,270]" italics="true" pageId="8">I</emphasis>
. cf. 
<emphasis box="[547,648,246,270]" italics="true" pageId="8">nigricans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
found in the Canadian Arctic by 
<bibRefCitation author="Curtis D &amp; Leys SP" pageId="8" pagination="1 - 102" refId="ref12395" refString="Curtis D, Leys SP. 2018. Field guide to Sponges of the Eastern Canadian Arctic. Edmonton: University of Alberta; p. 1 - 102." type="book chapter" year="2018">Curtis and Leys (2018)</bibRefCitation>
. Thus, the validity of 
<taxonomicName authority="Morozov &amp; Sabirov &amp; Zimina, 2019" authorityName="Morozov &amp; Sabirov &amp; Zimina" authorityYear="2019" box="[554,719,281,305]" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="8" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="koltuni" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[554,719,281,305]" italics="true" pageId="8">Iophon koltuni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[729,821,281,305]" pageId="8" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
removed any doubts.
</paragraph>
